within our energy field?

00:26:00.970 --> 00:26:04.030 align:middle line:84%
What's happening in
our biofield that

00:26:04.030 --> 00:26:08.700 align:middle line:84%
supports the transfer of
this energy to others?

00:26:08.700 --> 00:26:10.980 align:middle line:84%
To answer this, let's
take a quick look

00:26:10.980 --> 00:26:14.550 align:middle line:84%
at the heart's influence
on the biofield.

00:26:14.550 --> 00:26:16.860 align:middle line:84%
When the heart
beats, it generates

00:26:16.860 --> 00:26:21.360 align:middle line:84%
an electromagnetic field with
the strength of 2 and 1/2 watts

00:26:21.360 --> 00:26:24.240 align:middle line:90%
of energy in every pulse.

00:26:24.240 --> 00:26:27.660 align:middle line:84%
We can measure this field
up to at least 3 feet,

00:26:27.660 --> 00:26:30.360 align:middle line:90%
or 1 meter from the body.

00:26:30.360 --> 00:26:33.900 align:middle line:84%
But aura carries this
energy even further

00:26:33.900 --> 00:26:38.590 align:middle line:84%
reaching out to as far
as 50 feet from the body.

00:26:38.590 --> 00:26:41.550 align:middle line:84%
If we look at our
aura as a torus,

00:26:41.550 --> 00:26:43.200 align:middle line:90%
the heart is at the center.

00:26:43.200 --> 00:26:46.410 align:middle line:84%
And it pumps energies
through our field.

00:26:46.410 --> 00:26:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And this pumping amplifies
the electromagnetic effect.

00:26:50.580 --> 00:26:55.200 align:middle line:10%
As it pumps, that energy moves
through the toroidal flow.

00:26:55.200 --> 00:26:59.940 align:middle line:10%
And in the heart's center
is a spiraling vortex.

00:26:59.940 --> 00:27:02.470 align:middle line:90%
The brain emits a field too.

00:27:02.470 --> 00:27:04.720 align:middle line:90%
But it's much smaller.

00:27:04.720 --> 00:27:07.530 align:middle line:84%
And when the biofield of
the brain and the heart

00:27:07.530 --> 00:27:13.050 align:middle line:84%
are entrained together however,
the impact is much greater.

00:27:13.050 --> 00:27:16.290 align:middle line:84%
When we reach a coherent
state, that frequency

00:27:16.290 --> 00:27:22.620 align:middle line:84%
travels throughout the brain,
the body, and the aura.

00:27:22.620 --> 00:27:24.990 align:middle line:84%
And not only are we
creating coherence

00:27:24.990 --> 00:27:27.120 align:middle line:90%
in our inner structures.

00:27:27.120 --> 00:27:30.510 align:middle line:84%
We're affecting our
biofield as well.

00:27:30.510 --> 00:27:34.830 align:middle line:84%
Plus, then, when others
enter into our biofield,

00:27:34.830 --> 00:27:39.840 align:middle line:84%
they can be entrained into
the frequencies that we emit.

00:27:39.840 --> 00:27:42.030 align:middle line:84%
The greater our
state of coherence,

00:27:42.030 --> 00:27:46.050 align:middle line:84%
the stronger our resonance
is to entrain others

00:27:46.050 --> 00:27:48.520 align:middle line:90%
into that vibration.

00:27:48.520 --> 00:27:52.610 align:middle line:84%
Where does this gateway
of the heart take us?

00:27:52.610 --> 00:27:55.760 align:middle line:84%
Mystics have often talked
about that intelligence

00:27:55.760 --> 00:28:00.440 align:middle line:84%
of the heart which guides us
towards kindness, altruism,

00:28:00.440 --> 00:28:03.380 align:middle line:84%
and caring for the
well-being of all.

00:28:03.380 --> 00:28:06.320 align:middle line:84%
This intelligence is
not logical though.

00:28:06.320 --> 00:28:09.020 align:middle line:90%
It's based on compassion.

00:28:09.020 --> 00:28:12.830 align:middle line:84%
And it connects us
with the greater whole.

00:28:12.830 --> 00:28:16.580 align:middle line:84%
The heart guides us
towards kindness.

00:28:16.580 --> 00:28:19.070 align:middle line:84%
It becomes a gateway
through which we connect

00:28:19.070 --> 00:28:21.980 align:middle line:90%
to the whole of the universe.

00:28:21.980 --> 00:28:24.460 align:middle line:84%
From a quantum
perspective, there

00:28:24.460 --> 00:28:28.940 align:middle line:84%
is a vast amount of energy
stored within this frequency

00:28:28.940 --> 00:28:30.230 align:middle line:90%
spectrum.

00:28:30.230 --> 00:28:32.150 align:middle line:84%
And through the
gateway of the heart,

00:28:32.150 --> 00:28:36.320 align:middle line:84%
we can connect to the
holographic unity.

00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:41.000 align:middle line:84%
We bridge the individual
self with the greater cosmos.

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:42.800 align:middle line:90%
We maintain our sense of self.

00:28:42.800 --> 00:28:45.120 align:middle line:90%
But it's no longer a barrier.

00:28:45.120 --> 00:28:47.960 align:middle line:90%
We don't sense any separation.

00:28:47.960 --> 00:28:52.010 align:middle line:84%
And we connect to the
whole of the universe.

00:28:52.010 --> 00:28:54.890 align:middle line:84%
What are some steps
that we can take

00:28:54.890 --> 00:28:57.770 align:middle line:84%
to open this
gateway of the heart

00:28:57.770 --> 00:29:02.670 align:middle line:84%
and cultivate more compassion,
gratitude, and love?

00:29:02.670 --> 00:29:05.940 align:middle line:84%
Whether or not we can access
these energies ultimately

00:29:05.940 --> 00:29:11.490 align:middle line:84%
rests upon our own attitudes
of ourselves and our lives.

00:29:11.490 --> 00:29:14.650 align:middle line:84%
When someone sees
themselves as a victim,

00:29:14.650 --> 00:29:19.140 align:middle line:84%
it's because they've taken on
an outlook of separateness.

00:29:19.140 --> 00:29:23.370 align:middle line:84%
It's a feeling of powerlessness
where things are outside

00:29:23.370 --> 00:29:25.980 align:middle line:90%
seem more powerful.

00:29:25.980 --> 00:29:28.320 align:middle line:84%
When we feel powerless,
we then don't

00:29:28.320 --> 00:29:33.060 align:middle line:84%
feel good enough or worthy
enough to deal with things.

00:29:33.060 --> 00:29:36.210 align:middle line:84%
But it's our sense of
self-worth, self-love,

00:29:36.210 --> 00:29:40.260 align:middle line:84%
and self-acceptance that rests
at the core of our ability

00:29:40.260 --> 00:29:43.930 align:middle line:84%
to access this
gateway of the heart.

00:29:43.930 --> 00:29:47.740 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, this comes
down to two questions.

00:29:47.740 --> 00:29:50.100 align:middle line:90%
Can we love ourselves enough?

00:29:50.100 --> 00:29:53.460 align:middle line:84%
And can we be
grateful for our lives

00:29:53.460 --> 00:29:57.360 align:middle line:84%
even if we don't think there's
much to be grateful about?

00:29:57.360 --> 00:30:01.020 align:middle line:84%
In one study, participants
kept a gratitude journal

00:30:01.020 --> 00:30:02.850 align:middle line:90%
for six weeks.

00:30:02.850 --> 00:30:04.290 align:middle line:84%
And then three
months later, they

00:30:04.290 --> 00:30:07.590 align:middle line:84%
were given an exercise
to express gratitude.

00:30:07.590 --> 00:30:10.680 align:middle line:84%
Those who practiced the
gratitude journaling

00:30:10.680 --> 00:30:13.590 align:middle line:84%
showed significantly
more activity

00:30:13.590 --> 00:30:16.830 align:middle line:84%
in the medial
prefrontal cortex when

00:30:16.830 --> 00:30:21.120 align:middle line:84%
compared to the control group
who didn't do the journaling.

00:30:21.120 --> 00:30:24.510 align:middle line:84%
This was three months after
their gratitude journaling

00:30:24.510 --> 00:30:25.850 align:middle line:90%
had ended.

00:30:25.850 --> 00:30:30.360 align:middle line:84%
And yet the brain had
sustainably changed.

00:30:30.360 --> 00:30:32.760 align:middle line:84%
This suggests that
practicing gratitude

00:30:32.760 --> 00:30:34.830 align:middle line:84%
can help train our
brain to be more

00:30:34.830 --> 00:30:39.900 align:middle line:84%
sensitive to the experience
of gratitude long range.

00:30:39.900 --> 00:30:43.590 align:middle line:84%
It rewires our brain
and our outlook on life.

00:30:43.590 --> 00:30:46.590 align:middle line:84%
Practicing gratitude,
even if we don't feel it,

00:30:46.590 --> 00:30:53.310 align:middle line:84%
creates a shift within us to
start experiencing it more.

00:30:53.310 --> 00:30:54.840 align:middle line:10%
One way to start
working with this

00:30:54.840 --> 00:30:57.060 align:middle line:10%
is to start your own
gratitude journal

00:30:57.060 --> 00:30:59.430 align:middle line:10%
and make it a daily practice.

00:30:59.430 --> 00:31:02.520 align:middle line:84%
Just by committing to
the journaling practice,

00:31:02.520 --> 00:31:04.830 align:middle line:84%
you might start
looking for the things

00:31:04.830 --> 00:31:08.070 align:middle line:84%
to be grateful for as
you go through your day.

00:31:08.070 --> 00:31:10.440 align:middle line:84%
This then starts
shifting your perspective

00:31:10.440 --> 00:31:11.880 align:middle line:84%
on what we're
paying attention to

00:31:11.880 --> 00:31:15.140 align:middle line:84%
or focusing on
throughout the day.

00:31:15.140 --> 00:31:17.840 align:middle line:84%
When you find something
to be grateful for,

00:31:17.840 --> 00:31:21.500 align:middle line:84%
connect to the heart
in that moment.

00:31:21.500 --> 00:31:27.260 align:middle line:84%
Tune in and be fully present
with that moment of gratitude.

00:31:27.260 --> 00:31:30.290 align:middle line:84%
Even putting a hand
on her heart can

00:31:30.290 --> 00:31:35.030 align:middle line:84%
help us shift our focus
and body awareness.

00:31:35.030 --> 00:31:38.070 align:middle line:84%
Rather than feeling it for
a second and then moving on,

00:31:38.070 --> 00:31:41.360 align:middle line:90%
stay in that moment.

00:31:41.360 --> 00:31:44.420 align:middle line:84%
Be there in that moment
of time and learn

00:31:44.420 --> 00:31:48.530 align:middle line:84%
to amplify that
feeling of gratitude.

00:31:48.530 --> 00:31:52.710 align:middle line:84%
As we tune in and take time
to experience gratitude,

00:31:52.710 --> 00:31:56.600 align:middle line:84%
this also encourages
more oxytocin production.

00:31:56.600 --> 00:32:01.190 align:middle line:10%
And doing this will help us
come into a coherent state.

00:32:01.190 --> 00:32:03.920 align:middle line:84%
And as we amplify
the experience,

00:32:03.920 --> 00:32:06.786 align:middle line:90%
we prolong that state.

00:32:06.786 --> 00:32:09.410 align:middle line:84%
And this is something we
can do throughout the day

00:32:09.410 --> 00:32:12.770 align:middle line:84%
as we experienced
moments of gratitude

00:32:12.770 --> 00:32:16.860 align:middle line:84%
and again in the evening
when we journal it down.

00:32:16.860 --> 00:32:20.060 align:middle line:84%
As you do this, focus
on the heart center.

00:32:20.060 --> 00:32:23.960 align:middle line:84%
Focus on gratitude,
love, acceptance.

00:32:23.960 --> 00:32:26.300 align:middle line:90%
And also, acknowledge yourself.

00:32:26.300 --> 00:32:30.370 align:middle line:84%
This is about loving yourself
and accepting yourself.

00:32:30.370 --> 00:32:34.200 align:middle line:84%
Now, there are three areas to
focus on with this practice.

00:32:34.200 --> 00:32:36.770 align:middle line:84%
The first is to
include five things

00:32:36.770 --> 00:32:39.080 align:middle line:90%
that you're grateful for today.

00:32:39.080 --> 00:32:41.510 align:middle line:84%
These can be things that you're
grateful for in your life

00:32:41.510 --> 00:32:46.730 align:middle line:84%
in general or things you
experienced this day.

00:32:46.730 --> 00:32:51.980 align:middle line:84%
The second is to acknowledge
five things about yourself

00:32:51.980 --> 00:32:54.020 align:middle line:90%
and what you've accomplished.

00:32:54.020 --> 00:32:57.620 align:middle line:84%
If you've handled a stressful
situation with equanimity

00:32:57.620 --> 00:33:01.280 align:middle line:84%
or did something to be
proud of, acknowledge it.

00:33:01.280 --> 00:33:05.720 align:middle line:84%
This is about shifting to focus
on gratitude and love of self

00:33:05.720 --> 00:33:08.360 align:middle line:84%
rather than on all the
ways that we cut ourselves

00:33:08.360 --> 00:33:10.040 align:middle line:90%
down and criticize.

00:33:10.040 --> 00:33:13.370 align:middle line:90%
Let's affirm what we did well.

00:33:13.370 --> 00:33:15.950 align:middle line:84%
The third area to
journal about is

00:33:15.950 --> 00:33:20.210 align:middle line:84%
to acknowledge five things to
be grateful for in the world

00:33:20.210 --> 00:33:23.960 align:middle line:84%
or the universe or with our
connection to divine source,

00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:26.600 align:middle line:90%
something that is beyond us.

00:33:26.600 --> 00:33:29.690 align:middle line:84%
For example, we can
acknowledge our gratitude

00:33:29.690 --> 00:33:32.960 align:middle line:84%
towards the majesty
of eternal spirit

00:33:32.960 --> 00:33:36.670 align:middle line:84%
or towards the
beauty of the world.

00:33:36.670 --> 00:33:39.730 align:middle line:84%
Acknowledge the opportunities
and the freedoms

00:33:39.730 --> 00:33:44.580 align:middle line:84%
that we have to explore these
things in today's world.

00:33:44.580 --> 00:33:47.460 align:middle line:84%
Find things at a
philosophical level

00:33:47.460 --> 00:33:50.070 align:middle line:84%
that we can be grateful
for and connect

00:33:50.070 --> 00:33:53.190 align:middle line:90%
to the unity of all things.

00:33:53.190 --> 00:33:55.470 align:middle line:84%
And when you find
yourself moving out

00:33:55.470 --> 00:33:58.620 align:middle line:84%
of coherence or start
feeling stressed,

00:33:58.620 --> 00:34:02.370 align:middle line:84%
you can also practice
controlled breathing.

00:34:02.370 --> 00:34:04.860 align:middle line:84%
The breath is one
of the fastest ways

00:34:04.860 --> 00:34:08.130 align:middle line:90%
to influence our nervous system.

00:34:08.130 --> 00:34:11.489 align:middle line:84%
Focus on the breath as it
comes in through the nose,

00:34:11.489 --> 00:34:15.690 align:middle line:84%
travels down the throat, and
then bring it down to the heart

00:34:15.690 --> 00:34:18.630 align:middle line:90%
and even to the belly.

00:34:18.630 --> 00:34:22.139 align:middle line:84%
We want to really
slow down our breath

00:34:22.139 --> 00:34:25.980 align:middle line:84%
to five to seven
breaths per minute

00:34:25.980 --> 00:34:28.980 align:middle line:84%
in order to stimulate
that vagus nerve.

00:34:28.980 --> 00:34:33.300 align:middle line:84%
We can achieve this by
breathing into a count of five,

00:34:33.300 --> 00:34:35.730 align:middle line:84%
hold the breath for
a count of five,

00:34:35.730 --> 00:34:37.980 align:middle line:84%
and then exhale
to a count of 10.

00:34:37.980 --> 00:34:41.620 align:middle line:90%


00:34:41.620 --> 00:34:43.719 align:middle line:84%
Breathing out through
the mouth helps

00:34:43.719 --> 00:34:46.989 align:middle line:90%
to release more of the stress.

00:34:46.989 --> 00:34:49.300 align:middle line:84%
As you breathe,
bring your attention

00:34:49.300 --> 00:34:54.760 align:middle line:84%
to drawing that breath down into
the heart and into the belly.

00:34:54.760 --> 00:34:58.000 align:middle line:84%
Imagine the breath
drawing in energy

00:34:58.000 --> 00:35:01.900 align:middle line:84%
to activate the vagus nerve
traveling from the low brain

00:35:01.900 --> 00:35:05.510 align:middle line:84%
to all of the organs
and the heart.

00:35:05.510 --> 00:35:09.340 align:middle line:84%
Close your eyes and pull this
breath in through the nose

00:35:09.340 --> 00:35:11.380 align:middle line:90%
as it goes down.

00:35:11.380 --> 00:35:13.750 align:middle line:84%
It goes through the lower
regions of the brain

00:35:13.750 --> 00:35:15.640 align:middle line:90%
into the spinal column.

00:35:15.640 --> 00:35:19.180 align:middle line:84%
And this activates the
vagus nerve and the heart.

00:35:19.180 --> 00:35:21.690 align:middle line:90%


